item.title: What Genres Have You Tried?
item.dc:creator: sn.ow.y
item.description:
Oh boy, this list is gonna be long. I’ve tried a lot of genres, and only released a select number of tracks a long time ago. A lot of my projects are still sitting, unfinished so far.

Here goes:

  • cyberpunk: really well, that’s going to be my next album release
  • dubstep: I tried this a long time ago, to no avail
  • house: Pretty well
  • deep house: okay
  • Jazz: well, but I haven’t done a ton of it
  • lounge: actually surprisingly well; i was vibin’ here
  • ambient: not too bad, needs a tad bit of work
  • dnb/liquid dnb: mediocre
  • jungle (only once for the feb unicorn challenge): well
  • synthwave: well, but I haven’t released 90% of my projects here
  • techno: mediocre —> a bit better than mediocre
  • minimal techno/House-y stuff (idk the exact genre, take a look at a channel called cercle on YouTube for what I’m talking about): really well
  • trap: decent-ish, as I haven’t put a ton of time into it
  • future house: not too bad, but needs work
  • bass house: ehh
  • lo fi: pretty decent actually, and I want to put more work into this
  • future bass: i can’t tell if a couple of my first tracks are future bass, but if so, pretty good
  • future garage: I experimented with this briefly, and it wasn’t too bad
  • chiptune/video game themed stuff: pretty great actually, and the unfinished projects I have in this genre are some of my favorites
  • progressive house: tried this once, it was sort of good actually

If you got through all of this, thanks for reading!

Read full topic

item.title: What Genres Have You Tried?
item.dc:creator: Aadam
item.description:
Here is my genre checklist:

Techno: Obviously!!! I only do techno pretty much. It always goes well.
Trance: Heck yeah! I make a lot of trance. It turns out epic when I make trance.
Ultra Electronic: I invented this genre which is a mix of several ones. I only wish I was good.
Dubstep: I only tried a few times. It sounds alright.
Future bass: I am totally terrible, but I tried like a million times. Now I am improving.
DnB: Yeah, on the OG program once. It was okay. Now I tried some more times, and I am now good.
Trap: I think so! (I am still unsure if I did it tho)

Rock: I only find some distorted acoustic guitars and start making loops. It was not the best tho.
EDM: I am pretty sure I might have done it, and if I did, I think it might have been good.
Chill: I have tried a few times, although one of them is kinda dark. It turns out well.
Hardstyle: Okay…Keep Calm…
Deep house: Sure! Works well!
Wub Wub bass [not future bass but some other kind of wub bass]: definitely! It comes good!
I also make quick intense music, it is like DnB, same tempo, but different style beats. That works well.
A million other songs that I have no clue what the genre is whatsoever: K this one comes out good.

I will add more to the list soon!

Read full topic

item.title: What Genres Have You Tried?
item.dc:creator: Toveii
item.description:
Future House - This genre really depends on rhythm and I’m still getting better at it.

Jazz - Chords are the key to Jazz. I’m not great at it but I did some for fun.

Future Bass - I’m not much of a future bass producer, but I’ve experienced with it a couple times and they’re alright.

Melodic Progressive House - I really love this genre, and I don’t see much of any Auxy users make it. I’d say I’m decent at this genre. I found my drum selection for it.

Here’s all my main genres:
Lofi
Progressive House
